JOHANNESBURG - Khehla John Sithole has been appointed as the new national police commissioner, the Presidency revealed in a statement on Wednesday. He will take over the role with immediate effect. READ: New police commissioner could be appointed soon: Mbalula Sithole, born in Standerton in Mpumalanga, has a “wealth of operational as well as management experience in the SA Police Service,” the statement further read. The new top cop was the deputy national police commissioner for policing operations, a position he held since 2013. Sithole first joined the police in 1986 and was promoted to the position of lieutenant general in 2011. He completed courses in advanced financial management programmes as well as one for management development. The newly appointed commissioner also served as Free State provincial commissioner and has ambitious plans to bring down crime. eNCA